newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentina's Menem to visit Malaysia, Indonesia.
newsitem.headline: Argentina's Menem to visit Malaysia, Indonesia.

text.p: Argentine President Carlos Menem was scheduled to arrive in Kuala Lumpur on Thursday morning to start official visits to Malaysia and Indonesia, the Foreign Ministry said on Tuesday.
Menem was to be accompanied by Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella and a business delegation.
Menem's agenda in Malaysia included meetings with the Petronas oil company and Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad.
He was to leave on Monday for Indonesia and for a meeting with President Suharto.
